OL,3,CPlans to extend physician associate
OL,4,Croles rejected as 87% of doctors worry
OL,5,Cabout patient safety
OL,7,FDoctors have overwhelmingly rejected
OL,8,Fplans to increase the use of Physician
OL,9,FAssociates (PAs) in the NHS after a
OL,10,Fsurvey shared exclusively with ITV
OL,11,FNews revealed that 87% believe they
OL,12,Fcan sometimes be a risk to patients.
OL,14,FThe British Medical Association, who
OL,15,Fconducted the survey, claim it is by
OL,16,Ffar the biggest response to the
OL,17,Fsubject of unregulated PAs in the NHS,
OL,18,Freceiving nearly 19,000 responses from
OL,19,Fdoctors - including GPs.
